# Advanced Algorithm Implementations

This document catalogs all the advanced, research paper based, and god modded algorithm implementations in this repository.

## Sorting Algorithms

### Advanced Sorting Techniques
- **Block Sort** (`arrays_and_strings/sorting_searching/block_sort.cpp`)
  - Cache efficient sorting based on research paper
  - O(n log n) worst case, O(n) best case
  - Branch prediction friendly implementation

- **Smooth Sort** (`arrays_and_strings/sorting_searching/smooth_sort.cpp`)
  - Adaptive heap sort variant by Dijkstra
  - O(n log n) worst case, O(n) best case for nearly sorted
  - O(1) extra space using Leonardo numbers

- **Patience Sort** (`arrays_and_strings/sorting_searching/patience_sort.cpp`)
  - Card game inspired algorithm
  - Simultaneously sorts and finds longest increasing subsequence
  - O(n log n) time complexity

- **IntroSort** (`arrays_and_strings/sorting_searching/introsort.cpp`)
  - Hybrid algorithm used in C++ STL
  - Combines quicksort, heapsort, and insertion sort
  - Guarantees O(n log n) worst case

- **TimSort** (`arrays_and_strings/sorting_searching/timsort.cpp`)
  - Production grade algorithm used in Python and Java
  - Combines merge sort and insertion sort
  - O(n) best case for nearly sorted arrays

## Graph Algorithms

### Advanced Graph Techniques
- **Yen's K-Shortest Paths** (`graphs/graph_algorithms/yen_k_shortest_paths.cpp`)
  - Finds K shortest paths between two nodes
  - Based on research by Jin Y. Yen
  - O(K * n * (m + n log n)) complexity

- **Hopcroft-Karp Algorithm** (`graphs/graph_algorithms/hopcroft_karp.cpp`)
  - Maximum bipartite matching
  - O(sqrt(n) * m) time complexity
  - God modded implementation with failure links

- **Dinic's Algorithm** (`graphs/graph_algorithms/dinic_max_flow.cpp`)
  - Maximum flow in networks
  - Based on research by Yefim Dinitz
  - O(V^2 * E) worst case, O(V * E) for unit capacity

- **Suurballe's Algorithm** (`graphs/graph_algorithms/suurballe_algorithm.cpp`)
  - Find two edge-disjoint shortest paths
  - Used for network reliability
  - O(m log n + k) complexity

- **Heavy-Light Decomposition** (`graphs/graph_algorithms/heavy_light_decomposition.cpp`)
  - Decompose tree into chains for efficient queries
  - O(log^2 n) per query with segment tree

